      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "047be941b7c98229",
      "text": "There is an obvious writing environment that solved this problem decades ago - wiki. A conventional multi-tenanted wiki allows anyone to update a wiki page - say containing an email address - and it is then available to everyone else - in a canonical place. Problem solved (in the usual fuzzy pragmatic way that wiki solves problems). Wikipedia is a form of social transclusion."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
